\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Likelihood Ratio: If the data are assumed to be homoskedastic, the classic
 likelihood ratio presented in the notes is used.
 If the data are heteroskedastic, an LM-type test based on the scores under
 the null but using a covariance estimator computed under the alternative
 is computed.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Lagrange Multiplier: Computes the LM test using the scores and errors estimated
 under the null.
 The assumption about the heteroskedasticity of the residuals and whether
 the residuals are correlated are imposed when estimating the score covariance.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Wald: Computes the GC test statistics using a Wald test where the parameter
 covariance matrix is estimated under the assumptions about heteroskedasticity
 and correlation of the residuals.
 For more on covariance matrix estimation, see 
\family typewriter
vectorar
\family default
.
 
\end_layout

